=== Etymology ===
Named after [[w:Pallas|Pallas]], an [[asteroid]] that had been discovered two years before the element.<!--was: {{Gr.}} [[Παλλας]] (Pallas), alternate name for [[Athena]]-->

=== Noun ===
'''palladium''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''palladia''' ''or'' '''palladium''')
[[Category:Countable]]
[[Category:Uncountable]]
{{wikipedia}}

#(''countable'') a safeguard (''from a statue of Athena that was believed to safeguard the ancient city of Troy'').
#(''uncountable'') a metallic chemical element (''symbol'' Pd) with an [[atomic number]] of 46.

